---
const faqs = [
  {
    q: 'What does Designed to Elevate actually do?',
    a: 'We build the marketing system around a service business — websites, landing pages, local SEO structure, lead-generation paths, and the copy that ties it all together. The goal is a site and a flow that quietly does the work of explaining, qualifying, and converting visitors so the shop owner doesn’t have to do that part by hand.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Who is this built for?',
    a: 'Local service businesses — auto detailing, window tint, barbershops, home services, and similar small local brands. The kind of shop that runs on appointments, quotes, and repeat customers. If your business depends on getting found locally and earning trust before the first call, this is built for you.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Designed to Elevate is brand new — should that bother me?',
    a: 'The studio is new. The experience behind it isn’t. The system here was built running and growing a real service business — a detail and tint shop — over multiple years. The two live project examples on this page are real work, and the body of client work is being built out intentionally.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Do you guarantee rankings, leads, or revenue?',
    a: 'No. Anyone who guarantees specific rankings or lead counts in local marketing is bending the truth. What we commit to is a sound system: a clear page, proper SEO structure, a real lead path, and continuous improvement. That setup gives a shop the best honest chance to grow — but no one can promise outcomes.',
  },
  {
    q: 'How do we get started?',
    a: 'Send a quote request through the form on this page or email bilsonxnc@gmail.com. The first step is a short conversation to understand the shop, the offer, and what’s missing. From there you get a written direction and a project quote — no pressure either way.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Where are you based and who do you work with?',
    a: 'Based in Zanesville, Ohio. Local roots, but the work is built and delivered online — so we work with service businesses anywhere in the U.S.',
  },
  {
    q: 'How is pricing handled?',
    a: 'Project-based and quoted to the scope. Website builds, landing pages, and strategy sessions each have their own pricing path, and ongoing monthly support is month-to-month with no long contracts. Numbers come back in writing after the first conversation.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Do you only build sites, or do you handle marketing strategy too?',
    a: 'Both. The build and the strategy are connected here — the site is the system the strategy runs on. Some shops want a one-time build, some want ongoing support, and some just want a focused strategy session. All three doors are open.',
  },
];
---
<section class="faq" id="faq">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow"><span class="dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> FAQ</span>
      <h2>Common questions, plainly answered.</h2>
    </div>

    <ul class="faq-list" role="list">
      {faqs.map((f, i) => (
        <li class="faq-item reveal" data-faq-item style={`transition-delay:${i * 35}ms;`}>
          <button class="faq-toggle" data-faq-toggle aria-expanded="false">
            <span class="q">{f.q}</span>
            <span class="plus" aria-hidden="true">
              <span></span><span></span>
            </span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-panel">
            <p>{f.a}</p>
          </div>
        </li>
      ))}
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .faq-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0; margin: 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
  }
  .faq-item {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
  }
  .faq-toggle {
    width: 100%;
    background: transparent;
    border: 0;
    color: var(--white);
    text-align: left;
    padding: 22px 4px;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 24px;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 1.4vw, 1.2rem);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  .faq-toggle:hover { color: var(--blue-soft); }
  .plus {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    position: relative;
    width: 22px; height: 22px;
  }
  .plus span {
    position: absolute; left: 50%; top: 50%;
    background: var(--blue);
    border-radius: 2px;
  }
  .plus span:first-child {
    width: 16px; height: 2px;
    transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
  }
  .plus span:last-child {
    width: 2px; height: 16px;
    transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
    transition: transform .25s var(--ease);
  }
  .faq-item.open .plus span:last-child { transform: translate(-50%, -50%) scaleY(0); }

  .faq-panel {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-rows: 0fr;
    transition: grid-template-rows .35s var(--ease);
  }
  .faq-panel > p {
    overflow: hidden;
    color: var(--soft);
    padding-right: 60px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .faq-item.open .faq-panel {
    grid-template-rows: 1fr;
  }
  .faq-item.open .faq-panel > p {
    padding-bottom: 22px;
  }
</style>
